      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Woke culture\" is a broad and often debated term, generally referring to heightened awareness of social and racial injustice. Supporters see it as a positive drive toward greater equality and holding powerful institutions accountable. Conversely, critics argue it can devolve into performative activism or a form of ideological policing that leads to censorship. Ultimately, whether it's \"good\" or problematic often depends on how narrowly or broadly one interprets the term.",
